PRACTICAL 6: Managing VMFS Datastores
Prerequisites

• Practical 5 completed
• iSCSI storage connected

Steps

Log in to ESXi Host Client and go to Storage.

Click on New Datastore and select VMFS.

Provide datastore name and select available disk.

Use full disk or custom partition size as required.

Complete datastore creation.

Expand datastore to utilize unused LUN space if required.

Verify increased datastore capacity.

Create a second shared VMFS datastore using iSCSI.

Remove or delete a datastore when no longer needed.
